    "data": {
        "description": {
            "value": "<p>Lethargy poison is commonly used in hit-and-run tactics by drow and others who want their victims alive; the ambusher retreats until the poison sets in and the victim falls unconscious. Further exposure to lethargy poison does not require the target to attempt additional saving throws; only failing an saving throw against an ongoing exposure can progress its stage.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><strong>Activate</strong>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: 'Pathfinder2eActions'; font-size: 1.8em; display: inline;\">D</span>&nbsp;Interact (Injury)</p>\n<p><strong>Saving Throw</strong> DC 18 Fortitude</p>\n<p><strong>Maximum Duration</strong> 4 hours</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 1</strong> @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.xYTAsEpcJE1Ccni3]{Slowed} 1 (1 round)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 2</strong> slowed 1 (1 minute)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 3</strong> @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.fBnFDH2MTzgFijKf]{Unconscious} with no Perception check to wake up (1 round)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 4</strong> unconscious with no Perception check to wake up (1d4 hours). </p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
